Fantastic sushi for a great price! Super friendly staff. Great stop for a lunch break, grab your food which is made when you order so be patient and then grab a table in the arcade and enjoy!
Would surely recommend visiting this place. Great atmosphere, flavorful dishes, excellent service. Great work.
The Beef bulgogi is delicious! The service is usually good too. Great place to grab lunch if you’re in a rush in the downtown area. You get a nice size portion for the price too.
Sometimes it can be a little cold if you order a fried roll cuz they get so busy, but seriously still worth it. Great sushi.
Best sushi rolls downtown! Soup is also amazing.  Great place to stop for a quick inexpensive lunch.

Lunch special is a good deal. Rolls are small, but sushi is fresh. Salad is fresh. Will definitely come back for more.
Decent price and quick despite the rush, in a good location, good taste.

Some of the best sushi in town and really friendly staff. Great selection and I gotta admit I love the K-Pop that's always playing in the background. It's a tiny treasure. Check it out!

This is one of my favorite places to eat on my lunch break. The line is frequently to the door because of how wonderful is! The sushi is very tasty and affordable and regardless on how long the line is, you can usually get in and out rather quickly. I definitely recommend trying it out!

One of the best places to get sushi delivered in the downtown area. The prices for their specialty rolls are great, and the freshness of the food is fantastic. If you can walk to the arcarde, even better.
For the first time, it was great!

Wow this place is amazing. Being from out of town I wasnt sure what to expect from this "mall" of food, but we walked in to this little place and it felt very authentic, family type of place. Beef bulgogi and a roll were great for a late lunch to go! Would love to go back again tomorrow!
Good food, good value. If you’re looking for authentic Korean food, this is the place to go.
Best pork bulgogi I’ve had in Nashville.
Small restaurant. The food does taste authentic. Well overpriced for the amount of food you receive though.
Fast service
Great for lunch. Can't beat the lunch combo of two rolls and a soup or salad for $7.50 plus tax.

Great downtown Nashville lunch option in the Arcade. Lunch specials are generous. Some challenges with space at peak so if you can go before (e.g. around 11) or after (e.g. around 1) it is quicker & less nerve wracking.
So I basically go there because I want sushi and it's close to my job. It's really not the best sushi and they charge $.50 for 1/4 teaspoon of spicey mayo. Ridiculous.
Great staff and excellent food!

I was very happy to find this place! The bibimbap was delicious. You get a generous portion at a good price. The veggies are all fresh and seasoned well. The egg was cooked perfectly. I could do with less lettuce and more spice in the …

Pretty solid Korean restaurant. No room to eat inside but there is seating out in the Arcade. Try the All In roll!
I got the bulgoki with a bottle of Coke. The portions were great, and the rice was fresh. The beef tasted awesome, and it came with a potsticker, too.
I'm not really qualified to review sushi but it's reasonably priced, fast, and i liked how it tastes. Support businesses like the ones in the arcade tunnel or lose them.
The sushi was fantastic and service was nice!

Great sushi at a price you wouldn't expect! Seriously, the lunch combo is an amazing deal, two rolls of sushi AND a soup/salad for only 8.50? I go to this place every chance I get, by far my favorite place in Arcade Alley.

Normally the Sushi is Awesome but something has changed..today it didn’t taste fresh...it tasted like it has been sitting out all day..I was disappointed I hope that it goes back to the way it use to be..
Best sushi for the price in Nashville hands down!
BEST DAMN BULGOGI I'VE EVER TASTED! Seasoned just right. Sorry I didn't have time to take a pic. I couldn't stop. Definitely worth the $10.

Nice spot.

Super friendly staff and delicious food. There's usually a line for lunch time take out so call ahead if you are in a hurry. I usually wait about 10 min at most.

Great lunch. Tasty rolls. Great if your in trainers & T. Or for take out. Excellent hole in the wall!

I don't think I've ever had "real" sushi but I love sushi rolls, and the ones from Jimbos always taste great! For a low price you can get 2 small rolls (I recommend the crunchy rolls) and soup or salad. The thing that puts it over the top for me are how sweet this couple is. The nicest owners ever!!! Love it!!
